WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.760 --> 00:00:12.720
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

2
00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:37.880
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

3
00:00:44.240 --> 00:00:47.560
MAN: <i>This is a story from long ago,</i>

4
00:00:47.640 --> 00:00:51.280
<i>when the great mammoths</i>
<i>still roamed our lands.</i>

5
00:00:53.800 --> 00:00:56.960
<i>It's the story</i>
<i>of my two brothers and me.</i>

6
00:00:57.600 --> 00:00:59.440
<i>When the three of us were young,</i>

7
00:00:59.520 --> 00:01:03.200
<i>we were taught</i>
<i>that the world is full of magic.</i>

8
00:01:03.400 --> 00:01:06.240
(MAN CONTINUES
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

9
00:01:08.600 --> 00:01:12.360
<i>The source of this magic</i>
<i>is the ever-changing lights</i>

10
00:01:12.440 --> 00:01:14.640
<i>that dance across the sky.</i>

11
00:01:18.320 --> 00:01:20.200
<i>The shaman woman of our village</i>

12
00:01:20.280 --> 00:01:24.280
<i>told us that these lights</i>
<i>are the spirits of our ancestors,</i>

13
00:01:24.360 --> 00:01:28.920
<i>and that they have the power</i>
<i>to make changes in our world.</i>

14
00:01:32.520 --> 00:01:35.160
<i>Small things become big.</i>

15
00:01:37.600 --> 00:01:39.760
<i>Winter turns to spring.</i>

16
00:01:43.040 --> 00:01:46.600
<i>One thing always changes</i>
<i>into another.</i>

17
00:01:48.640 --> 00:01:51.840
<i>But the greatest change I ever saw</i>

18
00:01:51.960 --> 00:01:53.880
<i>was that of my brother,</i>

19
00:01:54.480 --> 00:01:59.480
<i>a boy who desperately</i>
<i>wanted to be a man.</i>

20
00:02:02.680 --> 00:02:04.800
-Get down.
-What?

21
00:02:05.160 --> 00:02:07.080
Get down! Get down!

22
00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:15.400
Kenai.

23
00:02:30.640 --> 00:02:32.960
-(ANIMALS GRUNTING)
-(BOY COUGHS)

24
00:02:35.720 --> 00:02:37.840
Never try to milk a caribou.

25
00:02:37.920 --> 00:02:39.680
-(GRUNTS)
-(GROANS)

26
00:02:39.800 --> 00:02:42.240
-(LAUGHS)
-(CLEARS THROAT)

27
00:02:42.320 --> 00:02:45.840
No. No, don't. No. Come on, don't. No.

28
00:02:45.920 --> 00:02:48.360
Hey. Will you two knock it off?

29
00:02:48.880 --> 00:02:52.000
That's all right.
After today, he won't treat me like that.

30
00:02:52.080 --> 00:02:55.240
Oh, right, the big manhood ceremony.

31
00:02:55.640 --> 00:02:59.080
Doesn't matter what the spirits say,
you'll always be our baby brother.

32
00:02:59.160 --> 00:03:02.080
-Well, wait till I get my totem.
-Baby brother.

33
00:03:03.640 --> 00:03:05.840
Hey, I said knock it off.

34
00:03:05.920 --> 00:03:09.200
The quicker we get these fish,
the faster we get to your ceremony.

35
00:03:09.280 --> 00:03:13.160
Let's all just try and get along
for a few hours. Okay, Denahi?

36
00:03:13.240 --> 00:03:15.480
-Whatever you say.
-Okay, Ken...

37
00:03:15.560 --> 00:03:17.880
So, what are we waiting for?

38
00:03:17.960 --> 00:03:20.600
(GRUNTING)

39
00:03:20.960 --> 00:03:22.600
(SITKA LAUGHS)

40
00:03:23.960 --> 00:03:27.280
-Whoo!
-Whoo!

41
00:03:27.440 --> 00:03:32.360
<i>When the Earth was young</i>
<i>and the air was sweet</i>

42
00:03:32.800 --> 00:03:37.240
<i>And the mountains kissed the sky</i>

43
00:03:38.600 --> 00:03:41.320
<i>In the great beyond</i>

44
00:03:41.400 --> 00:03:43.720
<i>With its many paths</i>

45
00:03:43.800 --> 00:03:47.760
<i>Man and nature lived side by side</i>

46
00:03:49.600 --> 00:03:53.800
<i>In this wilderness of danger and beauty</i>

47
00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:59.120
<i>Lived three brothers bonded by love</i>

48
00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:03.920
<i>Their hearts full of joy</i>

49
00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:06.400
<i>They ask now for guidance</i>

50
00:04:06.480 --> 00:04:10.840
<i>Reaching out to the skies up above</i>

51
00:04:12.040 --> 00:04:15.080
<i>Great spirits of all who lived before</i>

52
00:04:15.160 --> 00:04:17.920
<i>Take our hands and lead us</i>

53
00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:22.400
<i>Fill our hearts and souls</i>
<i>with all you know</i>

54
00:04:23.600 --> 00:04:26.280
<i>Show us that in your eyes</i>

55
00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:28.440
<i>We are all the same</i>

56
00:04:29.200 --> 00:04:33.800
<i>Brothers to each other</i>
<i>in this world we remain</i>

57
00:04:34.400 --> 00:04:36.880
<i>Truly brothers all the same</i>

58
00:04:36.960 --> 00:04:41.120
<i>Give us wisdom to pass to each other</i>

59
00:04:42.400 --> 00:04:46.320
<i>And give us strength so we understand</i>

60
00:04:48.360 --> 00:04:51.280
<i>That the things we do</i>

61
00:04:51.360 --> 00:04:53.520
<i>The choices we make</i>

62
00:04:53.600 --> 00:04:57.440
<i>Give direction to all life's plans</i>

63
00:04:59.360 --> 00:05:03.840
<i>To look and wonder</i>
<i>at all we've been given</i>

64
00:05:04.720 --> 00:05:09.040
<i>In a world that's not always as it seems</i>

65
00:05:10.720 --> 00:05:13.400
<i>Every corner we turn</i>

66
00:05:13.480 --> 00:05:16.040
<i>Only leads to another</i>

67
00:05:16.120 --> 00:05:20.520
<i>A journey ends but another begins</i>

68
00:05:21.880 --> 00:05:24.920
<i>Great spirits of all who lived before</i>

69
00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:27.680
<i>Take our hands and lead us</i>

70
00:05:27.760 --> 00:05:32.040
<i>Fill our hearts and souls</i>
<i>with all you know</i>

71
00:05:33.320 --> 00:05:36.040
<i>Show us that in your eyes</i>

72
00:05:36.120 --> 00:05:38.120
<i>We are all the same</i>

73
00:05:38.920 --> 00:05:43.680
<i>Brothers to each other</i>
<i>in this world we remain</i>

74
00:05:44.160 --> 00:05:46.320
<i>Truly brothers all the same</i>

75
00:05:46.520 --> 00:05:48.880
-Kenai's back.
-Kenai.

76
00:05:48.960 --> 00:05:52.600
Kenai, are you excited
about getting your spirit rock today?

77
00:05:52.920 --> 00:05:55.840
It's not a rock. It'll be my totem.

78
00:05:55.920 --> 00:05:57.120
ALL: Ooh!

79
00:05:57.200 --> 00:06:00.440
I'll probably get a saber-tooth tiger
for bravery,

80
00:06:00.520 --> 00:06:02.480
or strength, or greatness.

81
00:06:02.560 --> 00:06:06.080
-Something that fits me.
-A mammoth for your fat head?

82
00:06:06.160 --> 00:06:09.200
-Make sure you get that basket tied up.
-Don't worry.

83
00:06:09.280 --> 00:06:11.840
No stupid bear
is gonna get near this fish.

84
00:06:11.920 --> 00:06:13.640
Just tie it up.

85
00:06:13.720 --> 00:06:15.960
(IMITATES) Just tie it up.

86
00:06:16.040 --> 00:06:19.560
-MAN: She's back. Tanana's back.
-Come on.

87
00:06:19.640 --> 00:06:20.880
(CHILDREN SHOUT)

88
00:06:20.960 --> 00:06:23.240
-Come on, Kenai, let's go.
-Come on.

89
00:06:23.360 --> 00:06:25.640
CHILD: Tanana's got your rock.
Come on.

90
00:06:31.920 --> 00:06:35.040
<i>Great spirits of all who lived before</i>

91
00:06:35.160 --> 00:06:37.440
<i>Take our hands and lead us</i>

92
00:06:37.520 --> 00:06:41.960
<i>Fill our hearts and souls</i>
<i>with all you know</i>

93
00:06:43.120 --> 00:06:45.760
<i>Show us that in your eyes</i>

94
00:06:45.880 --> 00:06:48.600
<i>We are all the same</i>

95
00:06:48.720 --> 00:06:53.240
<i>Brothers to each other</i>
<i>in this world we remain</i>

96
00:06:54.000 --> 00:06:56.960
<i>Truly brothers all the same</i>

97
00:06:57.040 --> 00:07:01.960
<i>Brothers all the same</i>

98
00:07:02.720 --> 00:07:03.920
GIRL: Nana.

99
00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:08.640
-Hey, Nana.
-Well, hello there, sweetheart.

100
00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:11.080
What a big girl.

101
00:07:11.560 --> 00:07:13.280
(SQUEALING)

102
00:07:13.360 --> 00:07:19.200
When each of us comes of age,
the great spirits reveal to us a totem

103
00:07:19.280 --> 00:07:22.200
that helps guide us through our lives.

104
00:07:23.040 --> 00:07:25.840
Some of us use courage to guide us.

105
00:07:27.080 --> 00:07:28.880
Others patience.

106
00:07:31.200 --> 00:07:33.880
And some of us beauty.

107
00:07:37.040 --> 00:07:38.320
Kenai.

108
00:07:41.040 --> 00:07:43.560
-You nervous?
-(EXHALES) Excited.

109
00:07:43.880 --> 00:07:46.720
(CHUCKLES) You should be.
It's a good one.

110
00:07:47.560 --> 00:07:52.240
Kenai, I have been to the mountain
where the lights touch the earth,

111
00:07:52.320 --> 00:07:57.120
and the great spirits
have revealed to me your totem.

112
00:07:57.880 --> 00:08:03.760
To become a man, your actions
must be guided by one thing.

113
00:08:05.240 --> 00:08:08.560
Your totem is...

114
00:08:11.640 --> 00:08:13.040
Love.

115
00:08:14.080 --> 00:08:17.160
-What?
-Yes, love.

116
00:08:18.280 --> 00:08:20.280
The bear of love?

117
00:08:20.360 --> 00:08:24.880
A love that connects
and unites all living things.

118
00:08:24.960 --> 00:08:27.920
-Who wants to trade?
-There is no trading.

119
00:08:28.760 --> 00:08:30.680
Oh, Kenai,

120
00:08:31.120 --> 00:08:33.720
love is the most precious of totems.

121
00:08:33.800 --> 00:08:37.000
It reveals itself in unexpected ways.

122
00:08:37.760 --> 00:08:42.520
Let love guide your actions,
then one day you'll be a man,

123
00:08:43.160 --> 00:08:48.000
and we'll place your mark
next to those of our ancestors.

124
00:08:57.560 --> 00:08:59.080
(ALL CHEERING)

125
00:09:05.040 --> 00:09:06.560
TANANA: Oh.

126
00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:13.480
There he is.

127
00:09:13.560 --> 00:09:15.800
Come here, lover boy.

128
00:09:15.880 --> 00:09:18.600
-Leave me alone.
-Kenai, wait.

129
00:09:19.560 --> 00:09:21.880
-I'm sorry.
-What?

130
00:09:21.960 --> 00:09:24.560
Your totem, I think it's really great.

131
00:09:24.640 --> 00:09:27.360
-You do?
-Yeah. And I made you something.

132
00:09:27.440 --> 00:09:28.680
Really?

133
00:09:28.760 --> 00:09:31.560
Now when you skip around
loving everybody,

134
00:09:31.640 --> 00:09:34.280
-you'll smell so sweet.
-(KENAI GROANS)

135
00:09:34.360 --> 00:09:36.240
Well, isn't this nice?

136
00:09:36.320 --> 00:09:38.720
Instead of fighting,
you're giving each other flowers.

137
00:09:38.800 --> 00:09:42.560
Yeah, isn't it lovely?
He's so in touch with his totem already.

138
00:09:43.120 --> 00:09:45.920
Hey, dog breath,
go take care of the fish.

139
00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:49.080
Sure. Kenai loves me, he loves me not.

140
00:09:49.160 --> 00:09:53.000
Kenai loves me, he loves me not.
Kenai loves me, he loves...

141
00:09:53.080 --> 00:09:56.960
-Kenai.
-Someday I'm gonna just...

142
00:09:57.520 --> 00:09:59.680
-He's just such a...
-Hey, bonehead.

143
00:09:59.760 --> 00:10:02.920
Just because his totem is wisdom
doesn't mean he's wise.

144
00:10:03.040 --> 00:10:06.360
-I mean, look at him.
-Kenai loves me, he loves me not.

145
00:10:06.680 --> 00:10:08.800
-GIRLS: Hi, Denahi.
-Oh, hi.

146
00:10:09.200 --> 00:10:11.600
-(DOG SNAPS)
-(DENAHI SHOUTS) Let go!

147
00:10:11.680 --> 00:10:14.600
Yeah, the spirits messed up
on both of our totems.

148
00:10:14.680 --> 00:10:17.160
I felt the same way
when Tanana gave me mine.

149
00:10:17.240 --> 00:10:19.120
-Get out of here.
-No, really.

150
00:10:19.200 --> 00:10:23.280
I said, "The eagle of guidance?
What does that mean?"

151
00:10:23.360 --> 00:10:26.240
But now that I'm older,
I know it's about being a leader

152
00:10:26.320 --> 00:10:28.160
and keeping an eye on you two.

153
00:10:30.400 --> 00:10:32.840
I just want to get my handprint
on that wall.

154
00:10:32.920 --> 00:10:37.480
Just be patient, Kenai.
When you live by your totem, you will.

155
00:10:37.560 --> 00:10:39.640
-Really?
-Guarantee it.

156
00:10:42.720 --> 00:10:46.240
But come on, the bear of love?

157
00:10:46.320 --> 00:10:48.440
I mean, a bear doesn't love anyone.

158
00:10:48.520 --> 00:10:51.480
They don't think. They don't feel.
I mean, they're...

159
00:10:51.560 --> 00:10:53.240
(CHATTER)

160
00:10:53.720 --> 00:10:56.800
-They're thieves.
-You didn't tie it up, did you?

161
00:10:56.920 --> 00:10:57.920
Uh...

162
00:10:58.000 --> 00:10:59.680
You should get the totem of pinheads.

163
00:10:59.760 --> 00:11:00.960
SITKA: Knock it off.

164
00:11:01.040 --> 00:11:03.120
-We'll just make another basket.
-We?

165
00:11:03.200 --> 00:11:06.800
Oh, no. It took me two weeks
to make that basket.

166
00:11:07.400 --> 00:11:10.800
Get lover boy to do it.
He's the one always messing things up.

167
00:11:10.880 --> 00:11:14.120
-Typical Kenai.
-All right, I'll go get your basket.

168
00:11:14.680 --> 00:11:17.160
Kenai, wait. Kenai!

169
00:11:19.920 --> 00:11:21.560
What?

170
00:11:28.680 --> 00:11:30.680
(PANTING, GROANS)

171
00:11:30.760 --> 00:11:32.960
(GRUNTING)

172
00:11:34.080 --> 00:11:35.440
(BEAR GROWLS)

173
00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:46.040
-SITKA: Kenai!
-(GRUNTS)

174
00:11:47.040 --> 00:11:48.720
Kenai!

175
00:11:48.800 --> 00:11:51.840
-Where'd he go?
-If we're lucky, far away.

176
00:11:52.120 --> 00:11:54.000
-(GRUNTS)
-(KENAI SHOUTS)

177
00:11:56.400 --> 00:11:57.680
Kenai!

178
00:12:00.960 --> 00:12:03.920
-Kenai.
-Sitka, no, you gotta get out of here.

179
00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:05.840
-What?
-The bear. Behind you.

180
00:12:05.920 --> 00:12:07.240
(SITKA SHOUTS)

181
00:12:09.320 --> 00:12:11.600
Hey, bear, come on. Over here.

182
00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:14.000
Come on, bear, come this way.

183
00:12:24.960 --> 00:12:26.640
(DENAHI SHOUTS)

184
00:12:27.720 --> 00:12:28.880
Denahi!

185
00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:33.160
-Hold on.
-Pull.

186
00:12:37.760 --> 00:12:39.400
(BOTH SHOUTING)

187
00:12:50.000 --> 00:12:52.120
-(GROANING)
-(PANTING)

188
00:12:57.200 --> 00:12:59.240
(SHOUTING)

189
00:13:03.840 --> 00:13:06.040
Sitka. Sitka!

190
00:13:10.560 --> 00:13:12.800
(BEAR HOWLING)

191
00:13:31.120 --> 00:13:32.280
Sitka.

192
00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:43.680
(HOWLING)

193
00:13:44.560 --> 00:13:46.440
(PANTING) Come on!

194
00:13:50.160 --> 00:13:52.240
-Sitka!
-Sitka!

195
00:13:54.240 --> 00:13:56.320
Sitka. Sitka!

196
00:13:56.400 --> 00:13:59.160
-Sitka?
-Sitka, where are you?

197
00:14:00.240 --> 00:14:01.240
Kenai.

198
00:14:12.520 --> 00:14:13.760
No.

199
00:14:15.280 --> 00:14:16.960
Sitka!

200
00:14:18.760 --> 00:14:20.320
Sitka!

201
00:14:22.400 --> 00:14:24.520
Denahi, let's find him!

202
00:14:24.600 --> 00:14:25.960
Sitka.

203
00:14:27.080 --> 00:14:29.800
Sitka, where are you? Sitka!

204
00:14:34.960 --> 00:14:38.640
(MAN SINGS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

205
00:14:51.400 --> 00:14:54.480
(CHORUS SINGS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

206
00:15:01.800 --> 00:15:03.840
(MAN CONTINUES SINGING)

207
00:15:20.520 --> 00:15:22.920
(CHORUS CONTINUES SINGING)

208
00:15:32.280 --> 00:15:35.200
-You ready?
-For what?

209
00:15:35.280 --> 00:15:37.280
For going after the bear.

210
00:15:38.840 --> 00:15:42.960
I know what you're feeling,
but killing that bear is wrong.

211
00:15:43.400 --> 00:15:46.880
Wrong? Our brother is dead
and it's because of that monster.

212
00:15:47.320 --> 00:15:49.880
I don't blame the bear, Kenai.

213
00:15:54.640 --> 00:15:57.880
-I see.
-Killing the bear won't make you a man.

214
00:15:57.960 --> 00:15:59.280
Now you're trying to be wise.

215
00:15:59.360 --> 00:16:02.120
I'm trying to follow my totem.
Why can't you?

216
00:16:02.200 --> 00:16:05.280
You really think love
has anything to do with being a man?

217
00:16:05.360 --> 00:16:08.400
A man wouldn't just sit here
and do nothing.

218
00:16:08.920 --> 00:16:12.600
Kenai. Don't upset the spirits.

219
00:16:13.120 --> 00:16:16.560
(SCOFFS) Spirits.
Thanks for your wisdom.

220
00:16:42.040 --> 00:16:43.640
I've got to stop him.

221
00:16:52.040 --> 00:16:54.480
You left too soon, Sitka.

222
00:16:54.560 --> 00:16:57.120
Your brothers need your guidance.

223
00:17:40.760 --> 00:17:42.160
(TWIG SNAPS)

224
00:17:55.880 --> 00:17:57.560
(TWITTERS)

225
00:17:57.680 --> 00:18:00.000
(GASPS) Ha!

226
00:18:00.080 --> 00:18:01.520
(CHITTERS)

227
00:18:09.480 --> 00:18:11.360
(BEAR ROARS)

228
00:18:28.200 --> 00:18:29.680
(SHOUTS)

229
00:18:31.560 --> 00:18:34.720
(GROWLS, SNORTS)

230
00:19:10.840 --> 00:19:12.240
(HOWLS)

231
00:19:24.480 --> 00:19:26.040
(GASPS)

232
00:19:27.680 --> 00:19:29.080
(SHOUTING)

233
00:19:34.720 --> 00:19:35.880
Kenai.

234
00:19:57.200 --> 00:20:00.160
-(SHOUTS)
-(BEAR HOWLS)

235
00:20:02.200 --> 00:20:04.640
(HOWL ECHOES)

236
00:20:05.520 --> 00:20:07.840
(PANTING)

237
00:20:18.880 --> 00:20:20.040
(SCREAMS)

238
00:20:20.120 --> 00:20:21.680
(GASPS)

239
00:20:27.880 --> 00:20:31.800
(VOICES WHISPERING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

240
00:20:37.760 --> 00:20:38.960
What?

241
00:20:39.240 --> 00:20:42.360
(WOMAN VOCALIZING)

242
00:20:42.440 --> 00:20:45.560
(CHORUS VOCALIZING)

243
00:20:53.000 --> 00:20:55.680
-(PANTING)
-(THUNDER RUMBLES)

244
00:21:05.560 --> 00:21:08.560
(CHORUS CONTINUES SINGING)

245
00:21:12.360 --> 00:21:15.440
(WOMAN VOCALIZING)

246
00:21:17.560 --> 00:21:19.440
(CHORUS CONTINUES)

247
00:21:20.680 --> 00:21:22.640
(TRUMPETING)

248
00:21:52.400 --> 00:21:53.640
Sitka.

249
00:22:08.920 --> 00:22:10.160
(GRUNTS)

250
00:22:28.600 --> 00:22:30.040
(GRUNTS, GASPS)

251
00:22:36.600 --> 00:22:38.240
(GROWLING)

252
00:22:44.640 --> 00:22:46.440
(THUNDER CRASHES)

253
00:22:47.640 --> 00:22:49.560
-(GRUNTS)
-(BEAR HOWLS)

254
00:22:52.200 --> 00:22:53.440
No.

255
00:23:01.800 --> 00:23:03.080
(HOWLS)

256
00:23:48.960 --> 00:23:51.200
DENAHI: <i>I don't blame the bear, Kenai.</i>

257
00:23:54.640 --> 00:23:57.680
KENAI: <i>A man wouldn't just sit here</i>
<i>and do nothing.</i>

258
00:24:31.720 --> 00:24:33.400
(KENAI GROANING)

259
00:24:48.560 --> 00:24:52.880
So, Kenai,
you've decided to join the living.

260
00:24:53.080 --> 00:24:55.360
Ooh-hoo.
That's quite a bump you've got.

261
00:24:55.440 --> 00:24:58.400
That must have been one heck of a ride
down the rapids.

262
00:24:58.760 --> 00:24:59.880
Tanana?

263
00:24:59.960 --> 00:25:02.680
(GROANING)

264
00:25:02.760 --> 00:25:05.280
Ooh. (GASPS)

265
00:25:05.600 --> 00:25:07.360
Nana, you won't believe this.

266
00:25:07.440 --> 00:25:09.880
I was at the top of this rock,
and all of a sudden...

267
00:25:10.120 --> 00:25:13.120
(GRUNTING, GROWLING)

268
00:25:13.560 --> 00:25:15.640
Kenai, honey. Shh-shh-shh.

269
00:25:15.920 --> 00:25:17.760
I don't speak bear.

270
00:25:23.440 --> 00:25:24.680
No.

271
00:25:25.600 --> 00:25:29.400
No, no! No! (GASPS)

272
00:25:29.480 --> 00:25:32.360
(SCREAMS)

273
00:25:32.440 --> 00:25:36.760
All right! All right! All right!
Would you settle down? Settle!

274
00:25:36.840 --> 00:25:39.880
Kenai! Kenai...

275
00:25:39.960 --> 00:25:43.920
Kenai. Kenai. This isn't going to work.

276
00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:45.240
(SIGHS)

277
00:25:47.080 --> 00:25:50.800
Kenai, listen to me. Sitka did this.

278
00:25:52.720 --> 00:25:56.920
Strange. Spirits don't usually
make these kind of changes.

279
00:25:57.320 --> 00:25:59.840
Oh. Oh, my, my, my, my. (GASPS)

280
00:25:59.920 --> 00:26:03.120
Sitka must have something really big
planned for you. Yep, yep.

281
00:26:03.200 --> 00:26:05.840
You are going to get
a whole new perspective on things.

282
00:26:06.040 --> 00:26:10.400
(GASPS) Oh! Do you see
in black and white or color?

283
00:26:10.480 --> 00:26:14.040
Hey. Listen to me.
You got yourself into this mess.

284
00:26:14.120 --> 00:26:17.440
If you want to change,
take it up with your brother's spirit.

285
00:26:19.600 --> 00:26:23.840
You'll find him on the mountain
where the lights touch the earth.

286
00:26:23.920 --> 00:26:26.600
He'll help you make up
for what you've done wrong.

287
00:26:26.680 --> 00:26:29.480
But I didn't do anything wrong.

288
00:26:30.080 --> 00:26:32.320
Tanana? Tanana!

289
00:26:32.440 --> 00:26:35.360
Wait. I didn't do anything wrong.

290
00:26:36.520 --> 00:26:39.080
-I don't even know how to get there.
-MALE: What happened to them?

291
00:26:39.200 --> 00:26:40.280
MALE 2: I don't know.

292
00:26:40.360 --> 00:26:42.440
MALE: They were here.
Now they're gone.

293
00:26:42.520 --> 00:26:44.520
MALE 2: Yeah, that's pretty weird.

294
00:26:44.920 --> 00:26:48.760
So you're telling me you didn't eat them
and you have no idea where they are?

295
00:26:49.040 --> 00:26:52.440
-Uh-uh.
-Hey, hey, you. You just talked.

296
00:26:52.520 --> 00:26:55.680
(STAMMERS)
Just back away, real slow-like.

297
00:26:55.760 --> 00:26:59.480
-How did you do that?
-I knew you had them.

298
00:27:00.640 --> 00:27:01.920
CHILD: Are we there yet?

299
00:27:02.000 --> 00:27:04.720
MALE 3: Don't make me
turn this formation around.

300
00:27:06.000 --> 00:27:10.200
Hey. Wait. Come back.
I'm trying to find where the lights...

301
00:27:10.280 --> 00:27:14.920
-What's he getting worked up about?
-Maybe the goose pooped on him, eh?

302
00:27:16.840 --> 00:27:19.200
Oh, gee. He's looking over here.
Let's beat it. This way.

303
00:27:19.320 --> 00:27:22.400
-No, this way.
-Thank you very much.

304
00:27:22.480 --> 00:27:24.960
-Just stay still and...
-Hey, you two!

305
00:27:25.040 --> 00:27:27.160
-(BOTH GASP)
-Head down.

306
00:27:27.240 --> 00:27:29.160
I think he's seen us. Now what?

307
00:27:29.240 --> 00:27:32.000
-Act like we're not here.
-We're not here.

308
00:27:32.160 --> 00:27:34.320
-Shh! What are you doing?
-You said to...

309
00:27:34.400 --> 00:27:36.120
-Don't say anything. Shh!
-Okay.

310
00:27:36.200 --> 00:27:37.480
-I said, "Don't say anything."
-Um, excuse me.

311
00:27:39.080 --> 00:27:42.080
-Don't eat us.
-You won't like us, eh? We're gamey.

312
00:27:42.160 --> 00:27:44.160
Yeah. Eat hoof-for-brains over there.

313
00:27:44.240 --> 00:27:46.840
-Pine-cone breath.
-Crusty tail.

314
00:27:46.920 --> 00:27:48.280
-Twig legs.
-Big nose.

315
00:27:48.360 --> 00:27:49.360
(GASPS)

316
00:27:49.440 --> 00:27:51.800
-Sorry.
-You went too far that time.

317
00:27:51.880 --> 00:27:53.760
-Okay, I'm sorry.
-Guys.

318
00:27:53.840 --> 00:27:57.160
-Yours is bigger than mine.
-I'm not eating anybody.

319
00:27:57.280 --> 00:27:58.960
Oh, whew.

320
00:27:59.200 --> 00:28:01.880
-That's mighty decent of you, eh.
-My name's Rutt.

321
00:28:01.960 --> 00:28:04.240
-This is my brother Tuke.
-How's it going, Bear?

322
00:28:04.600 --> 00:28:08.800
-(SCOFFS) Don't call me that.
-Sorry, uh... (STAMMERS)

323
00:28:09.120 --> 00:28:12.880
-Mr. Bear?
-I mean, I'm not a bear. I hate bears.

324
00:28:13.000 --> 00:28:17.080
-Well, gee, you're one big beaver.
-No kidding, eh?

325
00:28:17.440 --> 00:28:20.200
Do either of you know
where the lights touch the earth?

326
00:28:20.560 --> 00:28:23.160
Yee... ahh...

327
00:28:23.520 --> 00:28:27.040
No. Uh, no. Sorry, bear... Er, beaver.

328
00:28:27.120 --> 00:28:30.720
I'm not a beaver, I'm a bear...
No, I mean, I'm not a bear.

329
00:28:30.800 --> 00:28:33.000
-I'm a man.
-(LAUGHING) Excuse me.

330
00:28:33.080 --> 00:28:35.680
I was transformed into a bear.

331
00:28:35.760 --> 00:28:39.400
Magically. I was lifted into the sky
by my brother.

332
00:28:39.480 --> 00:28:40.880
Uh-huh.

333
00:28:41.440 --> 00:28:43.200
-(SNEEZING) Crazy.
-Gesundheit.

334
00:28:43.280 --> 00:28:45.320
No. (SNEEZING) Fruitcake.

335
00:28:45.400 --> 00:28:48.320
-Are you okay?
-(SNEEZING) No. That bear. Over there.

336
00:28:48.400 --> 00:28:50.640
-He's crazy.
-I am not crazy.

337
00:28:51.520 --> 00:28:53.920
Whoever said you were?
We understand.

338
00:28:54.040 --> 00:28:56.200
-You do?
-Oh, yeah, yeah.

339
00:28:56.280 --> 00:28:58.360
You see, we're not moose either.

340
00:28:58.440 --> 00:28:59.960
-We're not?
-No.

341
00:29:00.480 --> 00:29:03.360
We're like, uh...
We're like squirrels. Yeah.

342
00:29:03.480 --> 00:29:06.160
Oh. Oh, yeah. Beauty, eh?

343
00:29:06.240 --> 00:29:11.040
Well, he's actually the squirrel.
I'm more of a purebred wolverine.

344
00:29:11.120 --> 00:29:13.320
Look at these cuspids. (GROWLS)

345
00:29:13.760 --> 00:29:17.720
-TUKE: Give him a little room.
-(GROANS) Why am I talking to moose?

346
00:29:17.800 --> 00:29:20.360
-No, we're squirrels, eh.
-Wolverine.

347
00:29:21.440 --> 00:29:23.440
I'll find it myself.

348
00:29:24.360 --> 00:29:26.840
-Oh, I wouldn't go that way.
-Why not, eh?

349
00:29:27.240 --> 00:29:29.920
Uh, well, there was a reason.

350
00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:32.360
TUKE: You brought it up.
RUTT: I'm trying to...

351
00:29:32.640 --> 00:29:34.360
(SHOUTS, GRUNTS)

352
00:29:34.680 --> 00:29:36.560
Ow! (GRUNTS)

353
00:29:37.360 --> 00:29:39.320
-(GRUNTING)
-(THUDDING)

354
00:29:39.400 --> 00:29:40.640
Ow!

355
00:29:40.720 --> 00:29:44.480
-So, you think of it yet?
-Well, no, but it's driving me nuts.

356
00:29:44.880 --> 00:29:46.760
Ow. (GROANS)

357
00:30:00.160 --> 00:30:02.120
Hey. Is the coast clear?

358
00:30:02.200 --> 00:30:04.960
-What?
-Are there any hunters around?

359
00:30:05.120 --> 00:30:07.480
-Uh... No.
-Oh, good!

360
00:30:07.560 --> 00:30:10.280
-(SHOUTS)
-You didn't see the trap?

361
00:30:10.360 --> 00:30:14.360
I saw it from a mile away.
You must be pretty embarrassed.

362
00:30:14.440 --> 00:30:15.720
Don't worry.

363
00:30:16.720 --> 00:30:19.200
(WHISPERS) I won't tell anyone.

364
00:30:19.400 --> 00:30:21.720
-What?
-You need to get down. Let me help.

365
00:30:21.840 --> 00:30:23.400
Oh, wait. Ow!

366
00:30:23.480 --> 00:30:26.080
-Hold still.
-Just... Stop that. Ow!

367
00:30:26.800 --> 00:30:28.240
If you just...

368
00:30:28.720 --> 00:30:31.240
-Stop it!
-It's no use.

369
00:30:31.600 --> 00:30:35.960
The only way to get down
is to chew your own foot off.

370
00:30:36.040 --> 00:30:39.960
I don't need some stupid bear's help.
I just need the stick.

371
00:30:40.080 --> 00:30:42.320
-Okay, here.
-No, I'll do it myself.

372
00:30:42.440 --> 00:30:45.000
Put it back. No, where you found it.

373
00:30:45.160 --> 00:30:47.960
-Oh.
-To the left. By the little rock.

374
00:30:48.040 --> 00:30:49.440
-Here?
-Yes.

375
00:30:49.520 --> 00:30:50.920
Okay.

376
00:30:52.080 --> 00:30:54.640
Boy, that tree is strong, huh?

377
00:30:54.720 --> 00:30:57.760
You know, when I was little,
I was really into climbing trees.

378
00:30:57.840 --> 00:30:59.120
All kinds of trees.

379
00:30:59.200 --> 00:31:04.960
I climbed pine trees, oaks, cedars,
maples, birch trees, willow trees...

380
00:31:05.040 --> 00:31:07.160
My eyes were watering
and my tongue was swollen.

381
00:31:07.240 --> 00:31:10.920
From that moment on,
I was more careful about what I lick.

382
00:31:11.280 --> 00:31:13.120
(GROANING)

383
00:31:15.240 --> 00:31:20.680
Ha! See? It's all about using your head.

384
00:31:22.960 --> 00:31:26.600
-(SHOUTS, GRUNTS)
-That was funny. Do it again.

385
00:31:26.680 --> 00:31:30.360
-Don't you have someplace to go?
-Yeah, the salmon run.

386
00:31:32.200 --> 00:31:35.520
How about this?
I get you down, then we go together.

387
00:31:35.600 --> 00:31:38.560
-Deal?
-Yeah, okay, fine.

388
00:31:38.640 --> 00:31:42.080
If you can magically get me down,
I'll go with you to this...

389
00:31:42.160 --> 00:31:45.200
-Salmon run.
-Whatever. But if you can't...

390
00:31:45.480 --> 00:31:49.560
You turn around, walk away,
and never come back, ever.

391
00:31:49.680 --> 00:31:51.400
-You swear?
-Yeah.

392
00:31:51.480 --> 00:31:54.400
-Pinky swear?
-Yeah, sure, fine, pinky swear.

393
00:31:54.480 --> 00:31:57.400
But this is a human trap
and you're just a dumb little bear.

394
00:31:57.520 --> 00:31:59.640
There's no way
you're going to be able...

395
00:31:59.840 --> 00:32:01.520
(GASPS, SHOUTS)

396
00:32:01.600 --> 00:32:02.840
(GROANS)

397
00:32:02.920 --> 00:32:04.840
(GRUNTS, GASPS)

398
00:32:05.240 --> 00:32:08.160
Okay, so I'm thinking
we travel by day and sleep by night.

399
00:32:08.240 --> 00:32:11.120
My bedtime is an hour after sunset...

400
00:32:11.200 --> 00:32:13.200
(SNIFFS, GASPS)

401
00:32:13.280 --> 00:32:14.640
Run!

402
00:32:15.120 --> 00:32:16.880
Yeah, good riddance.

403
00:32:17.160 --> 00:32:18.880
(SNIFFS)

404
00:32:27.520 --> 00:32:28.880
(GASPS)

405
00:32:31.920 --> 00:32:33.280
Denahi.

406
00:32:33.360 --> 00:32:34.760
Denahi, you found me.

407
00:32:34.840 --> 00:32:36.200
(GROWLING)

408
00:32:36.760 --> 00:32:38.600
You wouldn't believe
what a nightmare this has been.

409
00:32:40.320 --> 00:32:42.680
Denahi? It's me. Kenai.

410
00:32:43.560 --> 00:32:46.080
-(SHOUTING)
-(HOWLING)

411
00:33:00.440 --> 00:33:01.440
(PANTING)

412
00:33:08.160 --> 00:33:10.080
-(ICE CRACKING)
-(GASPS)

413
00:33:15.800 --> 00:33:17.600
Is he gone?

414
00:33:17.720 --> 00:33:19.480
-I think he was going...
-Shh!

415
00:33:19.600 --> 00:33:20.920
(MUFFLED)

416
00:33:26.640 --> 00:33:27.680
(SIGHS)

417
00:33:27.760 --> 00:33:29.840
CHILD: Hello. I can't breathe.

418
00:33:44.600 --> 00:33:47.720
-Why is he chasing me?
-That's what they do.

419
00:33:47.800 --> 00:33:51.520
-But it's not like him.
-Lucky for him, he didn't find us

420
00:33:51.600 --> 00:33:54.400
'cause when I get in a fight,
I go all crazy

421
00:33:54.480 --> 00:33:56.960
and I'm a raging ball of brown fur.
(GRUNTS)

422
00:33:57.960 --> 00:34:01.960
I mean, I don't want to brag or nothing,
but I got some moves.

423
00:34:02.400 --> 00:34:05.840
-Oh, really?
-Yep. This first one, well...

424
00:34:06.480 --> 00:34:10.000
It's just a little thing
I like to call "The Slasher."

425
00:34:10.080 --> 00:34:14.640
And this one I like to call
"Flying Fury of Death."

426
00:34:14.960 --> 00:34:18.240
-Uh-huh. He's coming back.
-Where?

427
00:34:18.800 --> 00:34:20.960
(SCOFFS) Typical.

428
00:34:21.040 --> 00:34:24.320
Yeah, well,
the next time we run into that hunter...

429
00:34:24.400 --> 00:34:28.120
There is no "we."
I'm not taking you to any salmon run.

430
00:34:28.320 --> 00:34:30.720
What? But you pinky swore.

431
00:34:30.800 --> 00:34:32.560
Yeah, well, things change.

432
00:34:33.400 --> 00:34:34.920
See you, kid.

433
00:34:36.600 --> 00:34:37.680
Wait, uh...

434
00:34:41.320 --> 00:34:45.080
The truth is,
I got separated from my mom.

435
00:34:45.160 --> 00:34:47.880
And now, with this hunter around...

436
00:34:47.960 --> 00:34:52.000
-Kid, I got my own problems.
-Come on. Please.

437
00:34:52.080 --> 00:34:55.960
Can't we just go together?
There's a lot of bears and a ton of fish,

438
00:34:56.040 --> 00:34:59.680
and every night we watch the lights
touch the mountain. Last year...

439
00:34:59.760 --> 00:35:02.760
-Wait, wait. What did you say?
-Lots of bears and fish.

440
00:35:02.840 --> 00:35:05.200
No. You know
where the lights touch the earth?

441
00:35:05.280 --> 00:35:08.240
Yeah! The top of the mountain
right by the salmon run.

442
00:35:08.320 --> 00:35:11.840
-You're kidding me.
-No, no, they're practically next door.

443
00:35:11.920 --> 00:35:14.280
Come on, I'll show you. It'll be great.

444
00:35:15.360 --> 00:35:18.880
I promise to help you escape
from every trap you walk into.

445
00:35:18.960 --> 00:35:20.720
I'm not going to walk into any more...

446
00:35:21.240 --> 00:35:26.200
-(GRUNTS) Traps.
-Come on. What do you say?

447
00:35:27.960 --> 00:35:30.600
Sure you can take me
to where the lights touch the earth?

448
00:35:30.680 --> 00:35:32.520
Yeah, no problem.

449
00:35:38.080 --> 00:35:41.280
-If you slow me down...
-I won't, I promise.

450
00:35:42.400 --> 00:35:44.880
All right, we leave first thing tomorrow.

451
00:35:58.320 --> 00:36:01.280
And keep all that cuddly bear stuff
to a minimum, okay, kid?

452
00:36:01.360 --> 00:36:04.280
My name's not "kid." It's Koda.

453
00:36:12.120 --> 00:36:13.760
What's your name?

454
00:36:19.640 --> 00:36:21.360
-Good day.
-How's it going, eh?

455
00:36:21.440 --> 00:36:25.760
Beauty. So we got a lot to get done
today. You want to get started?

456
00:36:25.840 --> 00:36:27.840
-Yeah. Just give me one sec, eh?
-Okay.

457
00:36:29.120 --> 00:36:31.400
Woo-oo-hoo...

458
00:36:31.640 --> 00:36:33.760
-Just help me crack this.
-All right.

459
00:36:33.960 --> 00:36:35.320
-(CRACKING)
-Ah.

460
00:36:35.400 --> 00:36:37.720
-You ready now?
-Almost.

461
00:36:39.520 --> 00:36:42.120
Just want to do "dog facing forward."

462
00:36:42.320 --> 00:36:46.160
-Oh, come on.
-Good. Okay.

463
00:36:46.240 --> 00:36:47.840
And go.

464
00:36:49.960 --> 00:36:51.520
This a nice patch here.

465
00:36:51.600 --> 00:36:55.080
Don't go near this patch here.
Something went here.

466
00:37:17.000 --> 00:37:18.320
Ahh!

467
00:37:22.320 --> 00:37:23.560
(GROANS)

468
00:37:35.640 --> 00:37:38.400
Skinny. Fat. Skinny. Fat.

469
00:37:38.480 --> 00:37:41.440
Hey, I've got a mountain to get to.
Come on, kid.

470
00:37:41.680 --> 00:37:44.960
I told you before. My name's Koda.

471
00:37:45.040 --> 00:37:48.080
Say it with me. Ko... Da.

472
00:37:48.160 --> 00:37:51.160
Sure your mom didn't ditch you,
Ko-duh?

473
00:37:52.000 --> 00:37:53.480
Humph.

474
00:37:59.640 --> 00:38:02.480
-Rutt.
-Go away, eh, I'm eating twigs.

475
00:38:02.680 --> 00:38:05.800
-Rutt.
-You're breaking my concentration.

476
00:38:05.880 --> 00:38:08.640
We should start running, like now!

477
00:38:08.720 --> 00:38:13.120
I can't. I'm still digesting, eh.
I'll get cramps.

478
00:38:18.960 --> 00:38:22.440
-Whoa, gee! He's after us!
-TUKE: Come on, little brother.

479
00:38:23.480 --> 00:38:25.000
(RUTT GROANING) Cramp!

480
00:38:26.000 --> 00:38:29.440
KODA: If you really want to know
how me and my mom got separated...

481
00:38:29.520 --> 00:38:34.000
I was saving this story
for the salmon run, but I'll tell you.

482
00:38:35.480 --> 00:38:40.320
It was probably the fifth or sixth
most coldest day in my entire life.

483
00:38:40.400 --> 00:38:43.480
-Sounds good. You should save it.
-You think so?

484
00:38:43.560 --> 00:38:46.040
-Oh, yeah. For your friends.
-Oh.

485
00:38:46.720 --> 00:38:49.200
-Well, I have this other story.
-Tell you what.

486
00:38:49.480 --> 00:38:52.400
-How about no talking?
-Okay.

487
00:38:53.000 --> 00:38:54.800
-Then I'll sing.
-No, no, no.

488
00:38:54.880 --> 00:38:57.440
(SINGING)
<i>Tell everybody I'm on my way</i>

489
00:38:57.560 --> 00:38:58.880
Will you stop it?

490
00:38:58.960 --> 00:39:01.000
<i>New friends and new places to see</i>

491
00:39:01.080 --> 00:39:02.680
Come on, quit it. Shh!

492
00:39:02.760 --> 00:39:05.520
-Koda, stop singing.
-(MUFFLED)

493
00:39:05.600 --> 00:39:08.040
<i>Yes, I'm on my way</i>

494
00:39:08.160 --> 00:39:12.560
<i>And there's nowhere else</i>
<i>that I'd rather be</i>

495
00:39:13.760 --> 00:39:17.640
<i>Tell everybody I'm on my way</i>

496
00:39:17.720 --> 00:39:21.560
<i>And I'm loving every step I take</i>

497
00:39:22.200 --> 00:39:26.560
<i>With the sun beating down</i>
<i>Yes, I'm on my way</i>

498
00:39:27.120 --> 00:39:31.040
<i>And I can't keep this smile off my face</i>

499
00:39:31.600 --> 00:39:36.280
<i>'Cause there's nothing like</i>
<i>seeing each other again</i>

500
00:39:36.640 --> 00:39:40.280
<i>No matter what the distance between</i>

501
00:39:41.160 --> 00:39:47.800
<i>And the stories that we tell</i>
<i>will make you smile</i>

502
00:39:48.120 --> 00:39:51.800
<i>Oh, it really lifts my heart</i>

503
00:39:51.880 --> 00:39:55.400
<i>So tell them all I'm on my way</i>

504
00:39:55.480 --> 00:39:59.760
<i>New friends and new places to see</i>

505
00:39:59.840 --> 00:40:04.800
<i>And to sleep under the stars</i>
<i>Who could ask for more?</i>

506
00:40:04.880 --> 00:40:08.400
<i>With the moon keeping watch over me</i>

507
00:40:09.200 --> 00:40:14.240
<i>Not the snow, not the rain</i>
<i>can change my mind</i>

508
00:40:14.320 --> 00:40:18.600
<i>The sun will come out, wait and see</i>

509
00:40:18.680 --> 00:40:22.400
<i>And the feeling of the wind in your face</i>

510
00:40:22.520 --> 00:40:26.240
<i>Can lift your heart, whoa</i>

511
00:40:26.320 --> 00:40:29.400
<i>There's nowhere I would rather be</i>

512
00:40:31.880 --> 00:40:34.640
<i>'Cause I'm on my way now</i>

513
00:40:36.840 --> 00:40:39.200
<i>Well and true</i>

514
00:40:41.600 --> 00:40:43.920
<i>I'm on my way now</i>

515
00:40:45.160 --> 00:40:47.440
RUTT: Hey, hold on, eh?

516
00:40:47.520 --> 00:40:48.680
KODA: Wait up.

517
00:40:48.840 --> 00:40:50.720
(RUTT AND TUKE PANTING)

518
00:40:51.040 --> 00:40:54.240
-How's it going, bear boy?
-And, uh, smallish bear.

519
00:40:54.320 --> 00:40:56.680
I didn't know you had a little brother.
He's cute.

520
00:40:56.760 --> 00:41:00.680
-Actually, he's...
-There was this hunter following us.

521
00:41:00.760 --> 00:41:03.960
We was thinking if we could
maybe just hang out with you guys.

522
00:41:04.040 --> 00:41:06.640
-Just hang out.
-Yeah, it'd be fun.

523
00:41:06.720 --> 00:41:09.960
-If the hunter was going to catch up...
-Then you'd eat him.

524
00:41:10.040 --> 00:41:13.640
-That's what we was thinking.
-We lost the hunter at the glacier.

525
00:41:13.720 --> 00:41:15.600
You don't think he'll follow those?

526
00:41:16.240 --> 00:41:20.400
-They are quite nice.
-I've got an idea.

527
00:41:20.480 --> 00:41:22.800
Okay, this is really weird.

528
00:41:22.880 --> 00:41:24.120
(TRUMPETS)

529
00:41:24.200 --> 00:41:27.320
-I'm driving.
-When can I have a turn?

530
00:41:27.400 --> 00:41:30.480
It's not as easy as it looks.
Just watch what I do.

531
00:41:30.560 --> 00:41:34.200
Let's get a back seat or something.
I look like you hunted me.

532
00:41:34.880 --> 00:41:37.880
<i>Tell everybody I'm on my way</i>

533
00:41:37.960 --> 00:41:39.240
Hey, come on.

534
00:41:39.320 --> 00:41:42.240
<i>And I just can't wait to be there</i>

535
00:41:44.000 --> 00:41:48.000
<i>Blue skies ahead</i>
<i>Yes, I'm on my way</i>

536
00:41:48.640 --> 00:41:53.080
<i>Nothing but good times to share</i>

537
00:41:53.200 --> 00:41:56.880
<i>So tell everybody I'm on my way</i>

538
00:41:57.760 --> 00:42:01.040
<i>And I just can't wait to be home</i>

539
00:42:02.480 --> 00:42:06.760
<i>With the sun beating down</i>
<i>Yes, I'm on my way</i>

540
00:42:07.360 --> 00:42:11.320
<i>With nothing but good times to show</i>

541
00:42:11.400 --> 00:42:14.800
<i>I'm on my way</i>

542
00:42:14.880 --> 00:42:18.680
<i>Yes, I'm on my way</i>

543
00:42:19.800 --> 00:42:21.200
RUTT: Beauty, eh?

544
00:42:22.600 --> 00:42:26.160
Okay, here's how I remember it.
The snow is white, it's all right.

545
00:42:26.240 --> 00:42:28.680
Yellow or green, it's just not clean.

546
00:42:28.760 --> 00:42:30.440
I learned that one the hard way.

547
00:42:30.720 --> 00:42:35.040
That reminds me. Last year at the
salmon run my friend Bucky dared me.

548
00:42:35.120 --> 00:42:38.240
But I'd heard of a cub
who stuck his tongue to an iceberg.

549
00:42:38.320 --> 00:42:40.200
Then he started to float away.

550
00:42:40.280 --> 00:42:43.040
To save him
they had to rip off his tongue,

551
00:42:43.160 --> 00:42:46.080
so now he hath to talk like thith
all the time and...

552
00:42:46.160 --> 00:42:49.000
-Do you ever stop talking?
-Oh!

553
00:42:49.080 --> 00:42:51.560
Look. The night rainbow.

554
00:42:51.640 --> 00:42:55.760
-You can see the spirits from here.
-You know about the great spirits?

555
00:42:55.840 --> 00:42:59.080
Yeah, my grandma's up there,
and my granddad.

556
00:43:00.280 --> 00:43:03.840
Mom says the spirits make
all the magical changes in the world.

557
00:43:04.040 --> 00:43:07.760
Like how the leaves change color,
or the moon changes shapes,

558
00:43:07.840 --> 00:43:11.480
-or tadpoles change into frogs.
-Yeah, I get it.

559
00:43:11.560 --> 00:43:16.080
You know, for a change, maybe
they could just leave things alone.

560
00:43:16.160 --> 00:43:19.200
-What do you mean?
-My brother's a spirit.

561
00:43:20.000 --> 00:43:22.160
If it wasn't for him, I...

562
00:43:22.240 --> 00:43:24.120
I wouldn't be here.

563
00:43:24.200 --> 00:43:26.400
You have a brother up there?

564
00:43:28.040 --> 00:43:31.840
-What happened to him?
-He was killed by a...

565
00:43:33.320 --> 00:43:35.320
By a monster.

566
00:43:40.840 --> 00:43:42.880
What's your brother's name?

567
00:43:42.960 --> 00:43:45.080
Sitka.

568
00:43:45.160 --> 00:43:49.360
Thanks, Sitka. If it weren't for you,
I would have never met Kenai.

569
00:43:54.880 --> 00:43:57.440
I always wanted a brother.

570
00:44:17.360 --> 00:44:19.480
RUTT: So, you want to play "I spy"?

571
00:44:20.080 --> 00:44:22.480
-All right. I'll go first.
-Okay.

572
00:44:22.560 --> 00:44:26.400
I spy something green.

573
00:44:28.680 --> 00:44:29.960
-Tree?
-Oh!

574
00:44:30.040 --> 00:44:31.200
-My turn?
-Yeah.

575
00:44:31.280 --> 00:44:34.280
Okay, I spy something tall.

576
00:44:35.920 --> 00:44:37.280
-Tree.
-Okay.

577
00:44:37.800 --> 00:44:42.440
I spy something with bark.

578
00:44:42.520 --> 00:44:43.840
-RUTT: Tree?
-(TUKE GROANS)

579
00:44:43.920 --> 00:44:46.560
Okay, I spy something, uh...

580
00:44:46.640 --> 00:44:48.960
-A vertical log.
-Tree.

581
00:44:49.720 --> 00:44:52.400
-Okay, I spy something...
-Tree.

582
00:44:52.960 --> 00:44:54.240
-My turn.
-Tree.

583
00:44:54.320 --> 00:44:55.520
-No, I...
-It counts.

584
00:44:55.600 --> 00:44:57.960
-I didn't even spy anything.
-It counts.

585
00:44:58.040 --> 00:45:00.280
Okay. Tree.

586
00:45:01.680 --> 00:45:03.760
Let's play something else.

587
00:45:09.720 --> 00:45:12.920
Koda. Come on.

588
00:45:13.000 --> 00:45:16.320
-Koda, wake up.
-Two more months, Mom.

589
00:45:20.040 --> 00:45:21.960
So, where are we?

590
00:45:29.720 --> 00:45:31.800
Well, which way?

591
00:45:33.400 --> 00:45:36.440
-I think it's that way.
-You think, or you know?

592
00:45:37.480 --> 00:45:38.560
That way?

593
00:45:39.880 --> 00:45:42.080
Why wasn't I turned
into a homing pigeon?

594
00:45:42.320 --> 00:45:45.760
-Come on.
-Hey, riding mammoths was your idea.

595
00:45:45.840 --> 00:45:48.240
Thanks for the ride, guys. See you.

596
00:45:48.320 --> 00:45:50.840
Lucky for you,
I've been lost worse than this.

597
00:45:50.920 --> 00:45:54.080
-Last summer, I was with Bucky...
-Enough with the stories.

598
00:45:54.160 --> 00:45:56.560
I don't care about the time
you and Binky found

599
00:45:56.640 --> 00:45:59.120
the world's biggest pine cone ever.

600
00:45:59.200 --> 00:46:03.080
First of all, his name's Bucky, not Binky.

601
00:46:03.200 --> 00:46:05.640
Second, it wasn't a pine cone,
it was a pine nut.

602
00:46:05.720 --> 00:46:08.800
And it was huge.
Even bigger than your fat head.

603
00:46:09.240 --> 00:46:11.480
Oh, gee,
our big guardian bear is leaving, eh?

604
00:46:11.560 --> 00:46:13.920
Yeah. We'd better follow him. Come on.

605
00:46:14.040 --> 00:46:17.120
-Can you swing your leg...
-I can't get off.

606
00:46:17.200 --> 00:46:19.960
Me, neither. Okay, you guys...

607
00:46:20.040 --> 00:46:24.040
I guess we'll just catch up
with those guys later, eh?

608
00:46:24.240 --> 00:46:26.960
-(SIGHS) Good trip, eh?
-Beauty.

609
00:46:27.040 --> 00:46:30.880
You know, I was thinking now
might be a good time for me to drive.

610
00:46:30.960 --> 00:46:33.520
Just relax and enjoy the ride.

611
00:46:33.600 --> 00:46:35.280
Yeah. Okay.

612
00:46:36.240 --> 00:46:37.640
Whee.

613
00:46:38.200 --> 00:46:41.200
I'm sorry we're lost, okay?

614
00:46:41.280 --> 00:46:44.120
-Even though it's your fault.
-My fault?

615
00:46:44.240 --> 00:46:45.640
(GROANS) That's it.

616
00:46:45.720 --> 00:46:49.400
Just remember, if it weren't for me,
you'd be hanging upside down.

617
00:46:49.480 --> 00:46:53.800
Better than being stuck nowhere
with you and your blabbering mouth.

618
00:46:53.880 --> 00:46:57.440
"I'm lost. I can't find my mommy.
Will you take me to the salmon run?"

619
00:46:57.520 --> 00:47:00.520
-Why don't you just grow up?
-Fine. I'll go on my own then.

620
00:47:00.600 --> 00:47:02.800
-Fine. Go ahead.
-Fine.

621
00:47:02.880 --> 00:47:04.200
-Fine.
-Fine.

622
00:47:10.920 --> 00:47:12.240
(SIGHS)

623
00:47:21.840 --> 00:47:23.280
KENAI: Koda?

624
00:47:24.000 --> 00:47:25.520
Koda?

625
00:47:33.840 --> 00:47:35.040
Whoa.

626
00:48:30.480 --> 00:48:33.000
Those monsters are really scary.

627
00:48:34.200 --> 00:48:36.240
Especially with those sticks.

628
00:48:53.360 --> 00:48:55.560
Come on, let's go.

629
00:48:58.800 --> 00:49:00.120
So, you recognize anything yet?

630
00:49:00.520 --> 00:49:02.960
Or maybe you can't see past
my fat head.

631
00:49:03.040 --> 00:49:04.520
(BOTH LAUGH)

632
00:49:06.200 --> 00:49:08.840
So, do you really think
I have a fat head?

633
00:49:08.920 --> 00:49:12.280
Well, if you hunched your shoulders
a little it wouldn't seem so big.

634
00:49:12.360 --> 00:49:14.800
Oh, you mean like this?

635
00:49:14.880 --> 00:49:16.720
-(LAUGHING)
-Or like this?

636
00:49:16.800 --> 00:49:18.800
How about this?

637
00:49:19.400 --> 00:49:21.960
Oh, my, that was good.

638
00:49:22.040 --> 00:49:24.120
KODA: Maybe they can
give us directions.

639
00:49:24.280 --> 00:49:26.200
-(BOTH GRUNT)
-Oh!

640
00:49:26.320 --> 00:49:28.120
-That clears up the sinuses.
-Oh, it does.

641
00:49:28.200 --> 00:49:30.440
Okay, okay, hit me again.
I think she's looking.

642
00:49:30.520 --> 00:49:34.800
-Hello, sweetie.
-Yes, she's checking me out, all right.

643
00:49:34.880 --> 00:49:37.320
-Hey, baby.
-No, come on, you nitwit.

644
00:49:37.400 --> 00:49:39.680
Are you out of your head?
She's looking at me.

645
00:49:39.760 --> 00:49:42.720
Like she's looking at your ugly mug?
Come on.

646
00:49:42.800 --> 00:49:45.160
Excuse me, miss. It's go-time, baby.

647
00:49:45.240 --> 00:49:47.240
You want to go? Bring it on.

648
00:49:47.320 --> 00:49:49.040
-Horns up.
-Hold on.

649
00:49:49.320 --> 00:49:51.840
-Excuse me.
-What do you want? (ECHOING)

650
00:49:52.080 --> 00:49:54.520
-What is that?
-Just a minute, bear.

651
00:49:54.640 --> 00:49:57.280
Hey, shut up. (ECHOES)

652
00:49:57.360 --> 00:49:59.520
No, you shut up.

653
00:49:59.640 --> 00:50:01.840
No, you shut up.

654
00:50:01.920 --> 00:50:03.920
Hey, will you shut up?

655
00:50:04.600 --> 00:50:07.360
-Just shut up.
-(ECHOING CONTINUES)

656
00:50:07.440 --> 00:50:09.800
Their horns are screwed on too tight.

657
00:50:11.920 --> 00:50:14.160
Oh, wait a second.

658
00:50:15.400 --> 00:50:17.800
-I know this place.
-You do?

659
00:50:17.880 --> 00:50:20.240
Yeah. The salmon run's not far.

660
00:50:21.120 --> 00:50:23.600
We just have to go through here.

661
00:50:36.880 --> 00:50:38.200
What?

662
00:50:41.600 --> 00:50:44.160
Hey, you sure you know
where you're going?

663
00:50:44.240 --> 00:50:46.240
Yeah, yeah, follow me.

664
00:50:53.640 --> 00:50:55.200
Koda?

665
00:50:57.680 --> 00:50:59.400
Koda?

666
00:51:01.760 --> 00:51:03.160
Koda?

667
00:51:03.800 --> 00:51:05.800
Where are you?

668
00:51:09.320 --> 00:51:11.680
-Yah!
-(SHOUTS, GRUNTS)

669
00:51:13.440 --> 00:51:16.560
-Don't do that.
-Scared you, didn't I?

670
00:51:16.640 --> 00:51:20.120
There's scared,
and then there's surprised.

671
00:51:20.200 --> 00:51:22.200
And you were both.

672
00:51:23.240 --> 00:51:24.440
Whoa!

673
00:51:34.520 --> 00:51:38.840
Nice try.
Uh, you got a little spit right there.

674
00:51:42.160 --> 00:51:45.360
-(GASPS) Kenai!
-You're not getting me this time.

675
00:51:45.440 --> 00:51:46.840
No, look out.

676
00:51:47.680 --> 00:51:49.040
(GASPS)

677
00:51:49.480 --> 00:51:50.760
(GRUNTS)

678
00:51:51.680 --> 00:51:52.880
No.

679
00:51:53.560 --> 00:51:55.200
Come on.

680
00:51:59.040 --> 00:52:00.360
(DENAHI YELLING)

681
00:52:03.520 --> 00:52:05.440
(CRIES OUT)

682
00:52:09.720 --> 00:52:10.760
Kenai.

683
00:52:14.040 --> 00:52:15.840
Kenai, where are you?

684
00:52:22.360 --> 00:52:23.680
(GASPS)

685
00:52:26.160 --> 00:52:28.720
Left. Left. No, the other left.

686
00:52:31.680 --> 00:52:33.840
-(GRUNTS)
-(TREE TRUNK CREAKS)

687
00:52:42.240 --> 00:52:43.320
Kenai!

688
00:52:47.080 --> 00:52:48.480
(DENAHI GRUNTS)

689
00:52:48.560 --> 00:52:50.240
Whoa! Whoa!

690
00:52:51.440 --> 00:52:53.760
-(GROAN)
-(GRUNT)

691
00:53:05.880 --> 00:53:07.560
No!

692
00:53:12.240 --> 00:53:14.440
What are you doing?
We got to get out of here.

693
00:53:16.120 --> 00:53:17.280
Ah!

694
00:53:20.840 --> 00:53:22.600
(PANTING)

695
00:53:27.680 --> 00:53:29.760
(PANTING)

696
00:53:46.160 --> 00:53:48.600
-(YELLING)
-(ROARING)

697
00:53:50.080 --> 00:53:51.720
(WHIMPERING)

698
00:53:52.480 --> 00:53:54.720
(GRUNTING)

699
00:54:01.640 --> 00:54:04.040
(ROARING)

700
00:54:08.880 --> 00:54:11.040
(PANTING)

701
00:54:23.560 --> 00:54:25.480
Why do they hate us, Kenai?

702
00:54:25.560 --> 00:54:27.680
-We're bears.
-So?

703
00:54:27.760 --> 00:54:30.920
So, you know how they are.
They're killers.

704
00:54:31.040 --> 00:54:33.320
Wait a minute, who's the killers?

705
00:54:33.400 --> 00:54:35.760
-Bears.
-What? Which bears?

706
00:54:35.840 --> 00:54:38.000
I'm not like that, and you're not like that.

707
00:54:38.080 --> 00:54:41.160
Well, obviously not all bears.
I mean, you're okay.

708
00:54:41.600 --> 00:54:45.560
Most bears will look for any excuse
to attack a human.

709
00:54:45.680 --> 00:54:48.280
But, Kenai, he attacked us.

710
00:54:50.760 --> 00:54:53.280
You're just a cub.
When you're older, you'll understand.

711
00:54:53.360 --> 00:54:56.040
(BIRD REPEATING) Fish! Fish! Fish!

712
00:54:56.120 --> 00:54:58.480
-Huh?
-KODA: We made it. We're here.

713
00:54:58.560 --> 00:55:00.880
-Come on!
-What? Koda.

714
00:55:00.960 --> 00:55:04.160
-BIRDS: Fish! Fish! Fish!
-Hey. Get away from me.

715
00:55:05.040 --> 00:55:07.440
Get away from me. Go on. Shoo!

716
00:55:09.920 --> 00:55:11.400
(GRUNTING)

717
00:55:11.480 --> 00:55:13.360
-(ROARING)
-(GASPS)

718
00:55:13.440 --> 00:55:16.360
-(GROWLING)
-(PANTING)

719
00:55:20.080 --> 00:55:21.160
(GASPS)

720
00:55:21.240 --> 00:55:24.240
(YELLING)

721
00:55:24.400 --> 00:55:26.240
