<i>Welcome to our family time</i>

796
00:59:47.640 --> 00:59:51.440
<i>Welcome to our happy-to-be time</i>

797
00:59:51.520 --> 00:59:56.520
<i>This is our festival</i>
<i>You know, and best of all</i>

798
00:59:56.600 --> 00:59:58.960
<i>You're here to share it</i>

799
00:59:59.040 --> 01:00:03.040
<i>We're here to share it all</i>

800
01:00:04.000 --> 01:00:06.120
(ALL LAUGHING)

801
01:00:10.560 --> 01:00:14.800
All right, settle down, everyone.
Settle down. Hey.

802
01:00:14.880 --> 01:00:17.560
Don't throw your fish bones there.
Somebody could choke on that.

803
01:00:17.640 --> 01:00:19.440
Look, okay, I'll go first.

804
01:00:19.520 --> 01:00:24.120
Okay, let's see. The most interesting
thing that happened to me this year.

805
01:00:24.240 --> 01:00:25.920
Hmm... (MUTTERS)

806
01:00:26.000 --> 01:00:28.200
Oh, I know, I know, I know! Listen to this.

807
01:00:28.280 --> 01:00:30.720
It was when I knocked down that tree

808
01:00:30.800 --> 01:00:33.040
that was blocking the view
from my cave.

809
01:00:33.520 --> 01:00:36.600
Now I got a family of chipmunks
staying in my place.

810
01:00:39.560 --> 01:00:41.240
(CLEARS THROAT) Yeah.

811
01:00:41.320 --> 01:00:44.080
All right, everybody,
let me see some paws in the air.

812
01:00:44.160 --> 01:00:47.200
-Who's gonna be next? Come on.
-Tug. I got one.

813
01:00:47.280 --> 01:00:50.240
Watch me. Hey, gotcha.

814
01:00:50.720 --> 01:00:55.200
This year I lost my dear husband Edgar.

815
01:00:55.280 --> 01:00:57.880
MALE: Quit telling everyone I'm dead!

816
01:00:57.960 --> 01:01:02.640
Sometimes I can still hear his voice.

817
01:01:02.720 --> 01:01:04.280
I'm getting the next one.

818
01:01:04.360 --> 01:01:07.760
(GROWLS,
SHOUTS IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

819
01:01:15.200 --> 01:01:17.040
(LAUGHING)

820
01:01:17.120 --> 01:01:19.080
ALL: Oh, yeah.

821
01:01:21.280 --> 01:01:25.640
-This is it. I got it. I got...
-I guess it's our turn.

822
01:01:25.720 --> 01:01:28.960
This is the year
I met the most gorgeous...

823
01:01:29.080 --> 01:01:31.160
No, you're gorgeous.

824
01:01:31.240 --> 01:01:34.800
-You're gorgeous-er.
-Get a cave.

825
01:01:34.880 --> 01:01:36.480
(GROANS,
SPEAKS FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

826
01:01:36.560 --> 01:01:38.520
If only Edgar was alive...

827
01:01:38.600 --> 01:01:41.200
EDGAR: I told you, woman,
I'm right here!

828
01:01:41.280 --> 01:01:45.320
-I love you, buttercup.
-This has got to be it.

829
01:01:45.400 --> 01:01:48.880
-Here you go, Koda.
-You gotta tell it, Kenai.

830
01:01:48.960 --> 01:01:52.080
-What?
-Yes. You caught it, you tell it.

831
01:01:52.160 --> 01:01:54.080
Didn't you play when you were a cub?

832
01:01:54.280 --> 01:01:56.480
-Um...
-FEMALE: Come on, Keno.

833
01:01:56.680 --> 01:01:58.960
(ALL CHATTERING)

834
01:01:59.400 --> 01:02:01.320
Okay, all right already. All right.

835
01:02:01.960 --> 01:02:04.400
-You want to know what I did this year?
-ALL: Yes.

836
01:02:04.480 --> 01:02:09.560
I went on the longest, hardest, most
exhausting journey I've ever been on

837
01:02:09.640 --> 01:02:13.080
with the biggest pain in the neck
I've ever met.

838
01:02:15.000 --> 01:02:17.440
What do you expect
from a little brother?

839
01:02:19.640 --> 01:02:21.640
Okay, buddy, your turn.

840
01:02:22.320 --> 01:02:25.320
-Let's hear it, Koda.
-Okay, okay, here we go.

841
01:02:25.440 --> 01:02:26.800
(CLEARS THROAT)

842
01:02:26.880 --> 01:02:29.720
This year I watched my mom
in a life-and-death struggle

843
01:02:29.800 --> 01:02:32.600
battling the most fiercest creature ever.

844
01:02:32.680 --> 01:02:34.280
-Who's next?
-What?

845
01:02:34.360 --> 01:02:39.080
Wait a minute. I think we all want
to hear the rest of that one, Koda.

846
01:02:39.160 --> 01:02:42.800
I thought you might say that.
Hmm... Let's see.

847
01:02:42.880 --> 01:02:47.440
It was probably the fifth or sixth
most coldest day in my entire life.

848
01:02:47.520 --> 01:02:50.600
Me and Mom were eating fish,
having a great time.

849
01:02:50.680 --> 01:02:55.680
All of a sudden she pushes me into
the bushes and tells me to be real quiet.

850
01:02:56.040 --> 01:02:59.560
She says, "I smell something."
So I started sniffing.

851
01:03:00.600 --> 01:03:03.280
There's something in the woods
running towards us,

852
01:03:03.360 --> 01:03:05.880
getting closer and closer.

853
01:03:06.040 --> 01:03:07.520
-(GASPS)
-(CHUCKLES)

854
01:03:07.600 --> 01:03:11.640
And then, out of the trees,
jumps a hunter.

855
01:03:11.720 --> 01:03:13.200
(ALL GASP)

856
01:03:13.560 --> 01:03:16.400
And now there's nowhere for Mom to go.

857
01:03:16.520 --> 01:03:20.200
The monster has her backed up
against this giant glacier.

858
01:03:24.640 --> 01:03:28.320
The monster attacks,
but Mom's too quick for him.

859
01:03:28.400 --> 01:03:33.920
And before he can do it again, she
stands up real big and yells, "Go away."

860
01:03:34.080 --> 01:03:35.880
-(SHOUTING)
-SITKA: <i>Kenai.</i>

861
01:03:36.000 --> 01:03:37.720
Mom smells more of them.

862
01:03:37.800 --> 01:03:39.840
There's a whole pack
coming right at us.

863
01:03:40.320 --> 01:03:42.320
Sitka, no. The bear. Behind you.

864
01:03:42.400 --> 01:03:44.720
<i>She runs to stop them</i>
<i>before they get to me.</i>

865
01:03:44.840 --> 01:03:47.880
<i>They're all around her,</i>
<i>poking her with sticks.</i>

866
01:03:47.960 --> 01:03:51.760
-KENAI: Sitka.
<i>-The whole thing broke and fell off.</i>

867
01:03:51.840 --> 01:03:53.680
<i>There was ice everywhere.</i>

868
01:03:53.760 --> 01:03:56.480
<i>She couldn't hold her breath</i>
<i>any longer, and pow.</i>

869
01:03:56.560 --> 01:04:00.520
She bursts out of the water.
I've never been so scared in my life.

870
01:04:00.800 --> 01:04:03.720
-KENAI: <i>I'm going after the bear.</i>
-Koda?

871
01:04:03.800 --> 01:04:05.680
DENAHI: <i>Sitka wouldn't want it.</i>
KENAI: <i>Sitka's not here</i>

872
01:04:05.760 --> 01:04:07.800
<i>because of that monster.</i>

873
01:04:09.960 --> 01:04:13.520
Whoa. Fell off a glacier?
I've never seen anything like that.

874
01:04:13.600 --> 01:04:15.720
-Can you imagine?
-(WHIMPERING)

875
01:04:16.360 --> 01:04:19.040
Kenai. What's the matter, Kenai?

876
01:04:19.120 --> 01:04:21.760
FEMALE: What happened next?
FEMALE 2: Was she okay?

877
01:04:22.880 --> 01:04:26.240
Hey, Kenai, what's wrong?
Where you going?

878
01:04:26.320 --> 01:04:29.520
She got out of the water okay.
That's how we got separated.

879
01:04:29.600 --> 01:04:32.520
Right after that I met Kenai.

880
01:04:32.640 --> 01:04:33.800
Kenai?

881
01:04:48.240 --> 01:04:50.560
(CHATTER, LAUGHTER)

882
01:05:18.680 --> 01:05:22.240
(ROARS) Scared you again, huh?

883
01:05:22.320 --> 01:05:24.200
-Yeah.
-Where have you been?

884
01:05:24.280 --> 01:05:25.880
-You look horrible.
-Koda...

885
01:05:25.960 --> 01:05:28.960
My mom says when
you eat too much fish, just lie down.

886
01:05:31.360 --> 01:05:33.360
There's something I, uh...

887
01:05:34.360 --> 01:05:36.520
You know that story
you told me last night?

888
01:05:36.600 --> 01:05:39.880
-Yeah.
-Well, I have a story to tell you.

889
01:05:40.000 --> 01:05:42.280
Really? What's it about?

890
01:05:42.360 --> 01:05:45.480
Well, it's kind of about a man,

891
01:05:45.560 --> 01:05:48.160
and kind of about a bear.

892
01:05:48.240 --> 01:05:51.280
But mostly it's about a monster.

893
01:05:52.640 --> 01:05:54.560
A monster who did something so bad...

894
01:05:54.640 --> 01:05:59.040
<i>Everywhere I turn I hurt someone</i>

895
01:06:00.280 --> 01:06:06.000
<i>But there's nothing I can say</i>
<i>to change the things I've done</i>

896
01:06:07.120 --> 01:06:10.680
<i>I'd do anything within my power</i>

897
01:06:10.760 --> 01:06:13.880
<i>I'd give everything I've got</i>

898
01:06:13.960 --> 01:06:18.560
<i>But the path I seek</i>
<i>is hidden from me now</i>

899
01:06:18.640 --> 01:06:21.840
Koda, I did something very wrong.

900
01:06:21.920 --> 01:06:26.120
<i>Brother bear, I let you down</i>

901
01:06:26.200 --> 01:06:27.840
I don't like this story.

902
01:06:27.960 --> 01:06:32.960
<i>You trusted me, believed in me</i>
<i>and I let you down</i>

903
01:06:33.040 --> 01:06:34.640
Your mother's not coming.

904
01:06:34.760 --> 01:06:38.080
<i>Of all the things I hid from you</i>

905
01:06:38.160 --> 01:06:40.920
<i>I cannot hide the shame</i>

906
01:06:41.000 --> 01:06:42.160
<i>And I pray someone</i>

907
01:06:42.240 --> 01:06:43.320
No. No!

908
01:06:43.440 --> 01:06:48.680
<i>Something will come</i>
<i>to take away the pain</i>

909
01:06:49.440 --> 01:06:52.840
<i>There's no way out</i>

910
01:06:52.920 --> 01:06:56.160
<i>Of this dark place</i>

911
01:06:56.280 --> 01:06:59.800
<i>No, no future</i>

912
01:07:03.240 --> 01:07:08.520
<i>I know I can't be free</i>

913
01:07:10.800 --> 01:07:14.400
<i>But I can't see another way</i>

914
01:07:15.880 --> 01:07:20.760
<i>And I can't face another day</i>

915
01:07:23.440 --> 01:07:26.480
Koda? Koda?

916
01:07:28.480 --> 01:07:30.200
Koda!

917
01:07:34.480 --> 01:07:36.080
Koda, I wish I could...

918
01:07:37.200 --> 01:07:39.920
If there was just some way...

919
01:07:41.160 --> 01:07:42.640
I'd give anything if...

920
01:07:45.800 --> 01:07:48.320
If I could just... (SIGHS)

921
01:08:00.120 --> 01:08:02.440
I'm sorry, Koda.

922
01:08:03.040 --> 01:08:04.800
I'm so sorry.

923
01:08:32.600 --> 01:08:34.520
(SHIVERING)

924
01:08:42.040 --> 01:08:44.040
I'm sorry, Kenai.

925
01:08:44.680 --> 01:08:46.840
I don't know what I'm doing anymore.

926
01:08:47.880 --> 01:08:49.880
I need help.

927
01:09:04.080 --> 01:09:05.560
Sitka.

928
01:09:16.040 --> 01:09:17.960
(EXHALES) Look, I am sorry.

929
01:09:18.040 --> 01:09:20.000
If I was driving
this never would have happened.

930
01:09:20.080 --> 01:09:25.400
-You never let me do nothing.
-Trample off. I said sorry. Let it go.

931
01:09:25.480 --> 01:09:27.800
I can't believe you totaled a mammoth.

932
01:09:27.880 --> 01:09:31.440
-That mountain came out of nowhere.
-I cannot accept your apology.

933
01:09:31.520 --> 01:09:35.240
-It was in my blind spot...
-Look. It's that little cub.

934
01:09:36.320 --> 01:09:39.400
-Gee, eh, something's bugging him.
-What's wrong, smallish bear?

935
01:09:39.760 --> 01:09:42.040
Nothing. I'm fine. (SNIFFLES)

936
01:09:42.280 --> 01:09:47.480
Good. Where were we? Oh, yeah.
You're a big, selfish, reckless hoofer.

937
01:09:47.560 --> 01:09:49.600
-What?
-I'm fed up with it.

938
01:09:49.840 --> 01:09:53.360
-From now on, he's my new brother.
-You can't do that.

939
01:09:53.440 --> 01:09:57.040
Sorry, you've been replaced
with my dear brother...

940
01:09:57.120 --> 01:09:58.920
What's your name again?

941
01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:01.360
I don't want any more brothers.

942
01:10:01.440 --> 01:10:05.280
-See? He's had enough of you, too.
-I promise I'll change.

943
01:10:05.360 --> 01:10:09.120
Trample off. You won't.
Being a brother means nothing to you.

944
01:10:09.200 --> 01:10:11.520
-Of course it does.
-Like what?

945
01:10:11.600 --> 01:10:14.040
What about when your hooves
froze in the pond?

946
01:10:14.120 --> 01:10:17.640
-Who sat with you all winter, eh?
-You did.

947
01:10:17.720 --> 01:10:19.880
Who showed you
where the good grazing is?

948
01:10:19.960 --> 01:10:23.400
The really tender stuff
all covered in dew.

949
01:10:23.480 --> 01:10:26.160
Now, why do you think I did that, eh?

950
01:10:26.240 --> 01:10:28.200
Because I...

951
01:10:28.280 --> 01:10:31.160
Because I love...dew.

952
01:10:31.240 --> 01:10:34.680
Excuse me?
I don't believe I heard what you said.

953
01:10:34.800 --> 01:10:37.840
I said, "I love dew."

954
01:10:38.480 --> 01:10:40.840
I love dew, too, eh.

955
01:10:42.160 --> 01:10:44.560
Hey, I can change.

956
01:10:44.640 --> 01:10:48.040
-Go away, eh.
-Come on, I can change.

957
01:10:48.120 --> 01:10:51.840
-Go away, eh, don't touch me.
-I can change.

958
01:10:51.920 --> 01:10:53.680
Hey. No.

959
01:10:53.760 --> 01:10:55.840
Not there, that's the spot.

960
01:10:57.800 --> 01:10:59.560
Like, we'll see you later, smallish bear.

961
01:10:59.640 --> 01:11:03.520
Yeah, good day, eh.
You know what this calls for?

962
01:11:03.600 --> 01:11:07.960
A pile of delicious barley and amber
weed on a cool bed of malted hops.

963
01:11:08.080 --> 01:11:10.080
I like it.

964
01:11:20.040 --> 01:11:22.800
(GRUNTING, PANTING)

965
01:11:26.520 --> 01:11:29.160
Sitka! Sitka, are you there?

966
01:11:30.360 --> 01:11:31.920
Sitka?

967
01:11:33.240 --> 01:11:37.480
Please. Please, Sitka.

968
01:11:37.560 --> 01:11:39.560
I don't know what else to do.

969
01:11:43.840 --> 01:11:45.040
Sitka.

970
01:11:51.960 --> 01:11:53.240
Denahi.

971
01:11:53.920 --> 01:11:55.240
(YELLING)

972
01:11:55.320 --> 01:11:57.320
Sitka, hurry, change me back.

973
01:12:09.720 --> 01:12:11.720
Where are you, Sitka?

974
01:12:12.280 --> 01:12:13.800
(YELLING)

975
01:12:34.680 --> 01:12:35.840
Denahi.

976
01:12:37.440 --> 01:12:39.040
Denahi, please.

977
01:12:43.520 --> 01:12:44.640
Koda.

978
01:12:53.480 --> 01:12:54.800
(GASPS)

979
01:12:55.800 --> 01:12:57.280
No!

980
01:12:59.360 --> 01:13:00.960
Leave him alone.

981
01:13:04.040 --> 01:13:05.400
Koda!

982
01:13:05.480 --> 01:13:07.440
(SHOUTING)

983
01:13:08.320 --> 01:13:10.560
-(GROWLS)
-(THUNDER)

984
01:13:31.320 --> 01:13:32.960
Kenai?

985
01:13:50.160 --> 01:13:51.680
Sitka?

986
01:14:02.000 --> 01:14:03.800
(KODA GRUNTING)

987
01:14:16.000 --> 01:14:20.480
Koda, don't be afraid. It's me.

988
01:15:08.120 --> 01:15:10.160
He needs me.

989
01:15:11.880 --> 01:15:15.360
You know, he did look better as a bear.

990
01:15:25.360 --> 01:15:28.600
But, Denahi...

991
01:15:29.280 --> 01:15:31.160
It's all right, Kenai.

992
01:15:35.600 --> 01:15:36.880
(GASPS)

993
01:15:38.960 --> 01:15:43.280
No matter what you choose,
you'll always be my little brother.

994
01:15:55.720 --> 01:15:58.760
(CHORUS SINGS
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

995
01:16:03.320 --> 01:16:04.640
Did I say little?

996
01:16:19.600 --> 01:16:21.680
(CHORUS CONTINUES)

997
01:16:38.680 --> 01:16:40.360
Kenai.

998
01:16:50.960 --> 01:16:52.760
(CHORUS CONTINUES)

999
01:16:52.880 --> 01:16:54.440
(ROARS)

1000
01:17:06.640 --> 01:17:11.720
DENAHI: <i>My brother Kenai went on</i>
<i>to live with Koda and the other bears.</i>

1001
01:17:11.800 --> 01:17:15.520
<i>He taught me</i>
<i>that love is very powerful.</i>

1002
01:17:15.600 --> 01:17:16.640
(ALL CHEERING)

1003
01:17:16.720 --> 01:17:20.400
<i>And I passed on the wisdom</i>
<i>of his story to our people.</i>

1004
01:17:21.720 --> 01:17:24.840
<i>The story of a boy who became a man</i>

1005
01:17:25.600 --> 01:17:27.680
<i>by becoming a bear.</i>

1006
01:17:28.080 --> 01:17:31.160
<i>Great spirits of all who lived before</i>

1007
01:17:31.240 --> 01:17:34.000
<i>Take our hands and lead us</i>

1008
01:17:34.080 --> 01:17:39.120
<i>Fill our hearts and souls</i>
<i>with all you know</i>

1009
01:17:39.560 --> 01:17:42.280
<i>Show us that in your eyes</i>

1010
01:17:42.360 --> 01:17:45.120
<i>We are all the same</i>

1011
01:17:45.200 --> 01:17:50.360
<i>Brothers to each other</i>
<i>in this world we remain</i>

1012
01:17:50.480 --> 01:17:53.440
<i>Truly brothers all the same</i>

1013
01:17:53.520 --> 01:17:58.480
<i>Brothers all the same</i>

1014
01:18:08.280 --> 01:18:10.720
(KARATE YELLS)

1015
01:18:10.800 --> 01:18:13.640
So, like, uh, what are you doing there,
smallish bear?

1016
01:18:13.720 --> 01:18:16.320
I'm practicing my moves.
Want to see one?

1017
01:18:16.400 --> 01:18:18.960
Sure, eh.
This ought to be good, eh?

1018
01:18:19.760 --> 01:18:21.840
-(LAUGHING)
-(BIRDS CHIRPING)

1019
01:18:24.080 --> 01:18:28.080
Listen to me. I was a man
that was changed into a bear.

1020
01:18:28.160 --> 01:18:31.600
No beaver. Man into bear. That's it.

1021
01:18:31.680 --> 01:18:35.720
Oh. Yeah, so, before that
you was probably like a goat?

1022
01:18:35.800 --> 01:18:38.040
-What about a water buffalo?
-No, he's a rabbit.

1023
01:18:38.120 --> 01:18:41.560
Look at his ears and furry feet.
Watch out for the rabbit, eh.

1024
01:18:41.640 --> 01:18:42.880
No way, eh.

1025
01:18:42.960 --> 01:18:46.760
Okay, now, everyone,
take a big inhale, eh?

1026
01:18:46.840 --> 01:18:48.320
And then on...

1027
01:18:48.400 --> 01:18:52.640
On the exhale,
shift into salutation to the sun.

1028
01:18:52.840 --> 01:18:54.600
(ALL GROANING)

1029
01:18:55.280 --> 01:18:58.280
-No, you shut up.
-(GRUNTING)

1030
01:18:58.360 --> 01:19:00.840
-No, you shut up.
-(GRUNTING)

1031
01:19:01.000 --> 01:19:02.400
(SIGHS)

1032
01:19:08.320 --> 01:19:09.800
(LAUGHS)

1033
01:19:09.880 --> 01:19:13.120
-How you doing over there, Koda?
-Oh, pretty good.

1034
01:19:15.720 --> 01:19:19.240
(BOTH LAUGHING, GROWLING)

1035
01:24:26.680 --> 01:24:28.080
(CLEARS THROAT)

1036
01:24:28.160 --> 01:24:31.600
In accordance with all federal
and state wildlife regulations,

1037
01:24:31.680 --> 01:24:34.360
no fish were harmed
during the making of this film.

1038
01:24:34.440 --> 01:24:36.040
(FISH SHOUTING)

1039
01:24:36.480 --> 01:24:39.480
-No! He's gonna eat me!
-(ROARS)

1040
01:24:40.160 --> 01:24:42.480
(NERVOUS LAUGH) Cut. Cut.

1041
01:24:43.040 --> 01:24:45.280
Somebody, help me.
Help me. Somebody.

1042
01:24:45.360 --> 01:24:47.160
-(CHOMP)
-Ooh!

1043
01:24:48.040 --> 01:24:49.920
(BELCHING)

